## Folder structure

```
{{ project_title }}/
    .github/           # CI workflow and the pull-request template
    .global-hydra/     # shared Hydra config groups: base, optimizer, scheduler
    .guidelines-ai/    # the conventions below — read these first
    .vscode/           # editor settings (ruff + ty wiring)
    experiments/       # one dir per experiment: goal.md + a Hydra config.yaml
        _template/     # scaffold that `just new <name>` copies
    packages/          # uv workspace members; the actual SSL code lives here
        core/          # the scaffold: data/model/loss contracts, training loop,
                       #   metrics, callbacks, loggers
        dummy-regression/  # a synthetic regression task wiring core end to end
    paper/             # the LaTeX article and slides (see paper/README.md)
    ressources/        # catalogued papers + docling conversion (see its README)
    scripts/           # entry points; train.py is the Hydra training launcher
    CLAUDE.md          # this file — project overview and guideline index
    README.md          # human-facing overview and getting-started
    justfile           # task runner: just run / check / new / list / paper
    pyproject.toml     # workspace root: deps, dev tools, Python pin
    uv.lock            # the resolved lockfile — uv owns it
    .python-version    # interpreter pin (>=3.14)
    prek.toml          # pre-commit hooks (ruff, ty, file hygiene, uv lock)
    ruff.toml          # lint + format rules
    ty.toml            # type-checker config
    pytest.ini         # test config — markers, doctests, importlib mode
    .gitignore         # ignored paths
```

The repo is a uv workspace (`[tool.uv.workspace]`, members `packages/*`). The
root is not itself a package; each subproject lives under `packages/`. `core`
holds the training scaffold, and `dummy-regression` is a worked example that
wires it end to end and is the one to copy when starting a new package.

## Running experiments

An experiment is a directory under `experiments/` with a `goal.md` and a Hydra
`config.yaml` that names the data, model, loss, optimizer, scheduler, eval
schedule, loggers, and callbacks. The config groups the experiments share live
in `.global-hydra/`. The `justfile` drives the common tasks:

```bash
just list                       # list experiments (skips the _template)
just new <name>                 # scaffold experiments/<name> from _template
just run dummy_regression       # train; extra args are Hydra overrides, e.g. seed=1
just check                      # ruff format + lint, ty, then the full test suite
```

`just run` calls `scripts/train.py`, which instantiates the config and hands the
pieces to `core.fit`. Metrics stream to the terminal and to `.logs/` through the
CSV logger.

